As part of measures to prevent the spread of Coronavirus, students of Moshood Abiola Polytechnic (MAPOLY), Abeokuta, Ogun State, have been told to stay at home. MAPOLY’s Public Relations Officer, Yemi Ajibola, confirmed the report to DAILY POST on Friday. Ajibola told our correspondent that, “the Bureau of Tertiary Institutions has sent a letter that all higher schools of learning should shut down as a result of the Covid-19 pandemic.” According to him, management of the polytechnic has directed all students to go home from Friday, March 20, until further directives.